Reasoning: The paper deals with modal logics and their sub-propositional fragments, which are topics that fall under the category of mathematical logic. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the satisfiability problem, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the paper introduces a measure of expressive power, which could make it relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as well. Finally, the study of fragments and their hierarchy could also make it relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
